key_events.description: Next dividend per share will be R$0.79, with an ex-date of January 16, 2026, and a payment date of January 23, 2026.
Average vacancy of 2.20%, with the general vacancy rate at 0%, but Jundiaí property presented delinquency above 20%.
BTG Pactual increased its exposure in BTLG11 by 3% in its recommended FII portfolio for January 2026.

risk_factors: Delinquency in Jundiaí property impacting overall vacancy metrics.

investment_thesis.bull_case: Potential for recurring income growth through lease renewals and contractual revisions, especially in properties near São Paulo. BTG Pactual increased its exposure in BTLG11 by 3% in its recommended FII portfolio for January 2026.
investment_thesis.bear_case: Delinquency in the Jundiaí property, with delinquency above 20%, could negatively impact income distribution. The average debt cost is IPCA + 5.91% per year.

summary_markdown: BTLG11 has an average vacancy of 2.20%, with a 0% general vacancy rate, but the Jundiaí property presented delinquency above 20%. The next dividend per share will be R$0.79, ex-date January 16, 2026, payable on January 23, 2026. BTG Pactual increased its exposure in BTLG11 by 3% in its recommended FII portfolio for January 2026. There is a potential for growth in recurring income through renewals and contractual revisions. 15th issuance BTLG11 of R$ 300 mi.
